title: Stocks to watch on Thursday
text:
Thu, Aug 13, 2015, 8:37 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 1 hr 23 mins Stocks to watch on Thursday AAP – 18 minutes ago 
Stocks of interest on the Australian Securities Exchange on Thursday: 
CWN - CROWN RESORTS - down 53 cents, or 3.8 per cent, at $13.52 
James Packer's casino giant Crown resorts reports its full year earnings on Thursday 
FXJ - FAIRFAX MEDIA - down two cents, or 2.4 per cent, 81.5 cents 
Media giant Fairfax reports its full year results. 
NWS - NEWS CORP - down 22 cent, 1.2 per cent, $18.70 
Romance books have helped Rupert Murdoch's News Corp deliver an 11 per cent lift in full year earnings. 
TLS - TELSTRA CORP - down seven cents, or 1.11 per cent, at $6.24 
Telstra has reported a one per cent slide in full year profit to $4.23 billion and lifted its final dividend half a cent to 15.5 cents. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Romance delivers for News Corp AAP
